He follows a very strict training regimen and likes to relax by deafeningly playing drums.

He was referred to Rhodes Island by [[Ebenholz (arknights)|]] after the events of [i]ZwillingstÃ¼rme im Herbst[/i]. [spoiler]He also assists the latter in his effort of rebuilding the territory of Urtica.[/spoiler]

title: lotus_eater
body:
The story of Lotus Eater has been in the works for over seven years, and we have been actively working on the story's art concepts for the past five years.

Lotus Eater: Ruination is the first of six main installments of the Lotus Eater story. From LE:R to the very final installment, each detail has been meticulously planned so that each of the six main arcs are woven together in ways that will make the reader want to revisit each installment again and again as new information comes to light.

Our ultimate goal is to create a Lotus Eater video game series based on our stories. Before that, we plan to distribute each installment as a printed novel, and later possibly as a series of graphic novels.
 
https://www.readlotuseater.com

title: alan_grant
body: Alan Grant is a fictional character in the [[Jurassic Park]] franchise. He is a paleontologist and is introduced in Michael Crichton's 1990 novel Jurassic Park, which began the franchise. Crichton based Grant on the paleontologist Jack Horner who was by happenstance technical advisor for the movies. Director Steven Spielberg helmed the 1993 film adaptation, and several actors were considered for the role of Grant. It ultimately went to Sam Neill, becoming one of his most popular roles. Spielberg gave the character a dislike of children, and put him in a relationship with [[Ellie_Sattler_(jurassic_park)|Dr. Ellie Sattler]], a paleobotanist who is Grant's student in the novel. Sattler, portrayed by Laura Dern, wants to start a family with Grant, who is resistant to the idea.

body:
Miyafuji Yoshika is the main character of [[Strike Witches]]. She has short [[brown hair]] and wears a [[school swimsuit]] under her blue [[school uniform]]. She is a part of the [[501st Joint Fighter Wing]]. Her affiliation however is the 288th Fuso Air Force, along with [[Sakamoto Mio]].

Her first [[Striker Unit]] was a A6M3a type Zero with a single yellow stripe as it's identification stripe. Her second unit was the same type (previously owned by Major Sakamoto Mio until she received a new unit based off of the [i]Kawanishi N1K-J [b]Shiden[/b][/i]) with blue stripes on the vertical stabilizer as well as a blue angled stripe that points downward at the front and upward at the back. 

Her third (and current) striker unit is based on the [i]KyÅ«shÅ« J7W [b]Shinden[/b][/i]. The [i]Shinden[/i] allows Yoshika to use her magic to her fullest potential, as during episode 8 of the anime (Strike Witches 2) her magic became so strong that the governor installed on Mio's striker unit protected the magic engine from overloading.

Her familiar is the [[shiba inu]].

title: atlas_gundam
body:
A fictional manned giant robot from the [[Gundam]] [[mecha]]verse. It first appeared in [[Gundam Thunderbolt]].

[b]RX-78AL Atlas Gundam[/b]

An amphibious land combat mobile suit developed by the [[Earth Federation]] to combat [[Zeon]]s highly dangerous amphibious mobile suits. 

The Atlas Gundam was equipped with a Globe Joint system as well as a powerful handheld railgun, along with the sub-legs system for increased mobility and weapon storage, as well as the heat resistant Blade Shield.

title: act_zaku
body:
A fictional military manned robot from the [[Gundam]] [[mecha]]verse. It first appeared in the [[Zeta Gundam]] TV series from 1985.

[b]MS-11 Act Zaku[/b]

A late development of the original [[Zaku II]] [[mobile suit]], the purple colored Act Zaku notably used field motors for its joints, rather than the fluid pulse system used by most [[Zeon]] MS. Its joints underwent magnet coating treatment, greatly improving its mobility. Thanks to improved generator output, it was able to use beam weapons, including a custom beam rifle. 

Following the end of [[mobile_suit_gundam|The One Year War]], the [[Earth Federation]] began mass producing the Act Zaku now with dark blue colors. The Federation-produced units were equipped with a linear seat cockpit, the BR-87A [[Beam Rifle]] used by the similar looking [[Hizack]], as well as a pair of beam sabers.

body:
A fictional manned giant robot from the [[Gundam]] [[mecha]]verse.

[b]RGM-79 [G] GM Sniper[/b]

An [[Earth Federation]] modification of the [[Ground GM]] [[mobile_suit|MS]] intended for long range fire support. It is equipped with a larger backpack and loaded a massive beam [[sniper rifle]] that could only be fired twice, with a long charging time in between shots, without an external power source. title: grey_hair
body:
Hair that is colored grey.

Due to the subjective nature of color judgment and other factors (such as differences in color displayed on monitors) there is potential overlap between this tag and the [[blue hair]], [[aqua hair]], and [[purple hair]] tags, generally in the lighter shades of those colors. Grey is also often used to shade [[white hair]]. It is a good idea to compare the hair in question to how other white things, namely white clothes, are shaded. If the shading on the hair resembles how white clothing is shaded, it is likely white, and not grey.

title: spike_spiegel
body:
The main character of [[Cowboy Bebop]].

A bounty hunter with an affinity for [i]jeet kune do[/i], he hunts down criminals who escape the grasp of the Inter-Solar System Police (ISSP) with the help of his partner, former Ganymede policeman [[Jet Black]] on the ship known as the Bebop. Spike does not always succeed in getting a bounty, and his penchant for causing massive destruction when in pursuit of a bounty head means that the bounties that he and Jet do get do not last long.

Spike also has a hidden past that involves the Red Dragon, a crime syndicate modeled on the Chinese Triads, and in particular the ruthless assassin known as [[vicious_(cowboy_bebop)|Vicious]]. Also figuring big into Spike's past is the mysterious woman known as [[julia_(cowboy_bebop)|Julia]], who Spike and Vicious both loved.

Spike's weapon of choice is an [[IWI Jericho 941]], and when chasing bounty heads, his vehicle of choice is the [[Swordfish II]], an Asteroid racer outfitted with four machine guns, missile pylons, and a plasma cannon.

Voiced in Japan by KÅichi Yamadera and in America dub by Steven Jay Blum.

title: haku_(utawarerumono)
body:
Haku is an amnesiac man found by [[kuon (utawarerumono)|Kuon]]. This encounter will eventually lead him to bond with a certain mercenary named Ukon (actually [[oshtor|Oshutoru]], Imperial Guard of the Right, in disguise) as well as start living in the Imperial Capital of Yamato, where he works as the Secret Agent of the aforementioned Oshutoru [spoilers]and uncovers a conspiracy against the Mikado of Yamato, his long lost brother who somehow significantly extended his lifespan. He is a true human who was sleeping in stasis since shortly before Iceman's wrath and somehow didn't become a Tatari.[/spoilers] 

At the end of Itsuwari no Kamen, [spoilers]he is forced to take Oshutoru's identity after his death and must lead a rebellion to restore Anju (the Mikado's daughter and heiress) as Yamato's Mikado.[/spoilers] At the end of his journey, [spoilers]Haku will find the true instigator of the conspiracy and become the new host of Wistalnemetia.[/spoilers]

He is the protagonist of [[utawarerumono: itsuwari no kamen|Itsuwari no Kamen]] and [[utawarerumono: futari no hakuoro|Futari no Hakuoro]] [spoilers] (in disguise as Oshutoru). [/spoilers]

title: arepa
body:
Arepa is a type of food made of ground maize dough, originating from pre-Columbian northern region of South America, and is notable in the cuisines of [[Colombia]] and [[Venezuela]].

It is eaten daily in those countries and can be served with accompaniments such as cheese, cuajada (fermented milk), various meats, chicken, avocado, and diablito. It can also be split to make sandwiches. Sizes, maize types, and added ingredients vary its preparation. Arepas can also be found in the Canary Islands. It is similar in shape to the Mexican gordita and the Salvadoran pupusa.

The word "arepa" comes from the indigenous term "erepa", which means "corn" in the language of the Cumanagoto people.

h4. See Also

* [[Tag Group:Food Tags]]

title: tone_rion
body:
Tone Rion is a Japanese [[VOCALOID]] developed and distributed by the YAMAHA Corporation in collaboration with Dear Stage (Moe Japan, Co. Ltd.), and was released for the VOCALOID3 engine. The software was updated for VOCALOID4 in 2017, and was subsequently released alongside [[yumemi nemu (vocaloid)|Yumemi Nemu]].

Said to be designed to sell to "moe" and otaku based culture, she is meant to sound cute. She was illustrated by [[Watanabe Akio]]. She has [[purple hair]] (in [[twintails]]) and [[purple eyes]]. Her features show her with a single [[fang]] tooth and [[blush stickers]]. She wears a pink [[maid]]-like outfit, [[necktie]] with jeweled [[choker]], [[fingerless gloves]], [[bracelet]]s, and [[thigh boots]]. She also wears a [[hat]], [[headset]], and a [[large bow|large buttbow]]. 

Her [[tone_rion_(vocaloid4)|V4 redesign]] was done by [[Horiguchi Yukiko]]. This version of her has long [[pink hair]] in [[twintails]] and [[blue eyes]]. She wears a [[cropped_jacket|cropped]] pink [[jacket]] over a pink shirt and [[puffy shorts]]. Her hat is gone, but she still retains her [[headset]]. She wears white [[thigh boots]] over grey [[pantyhose]].

Her motif animal is the [[rabbit]].

Her voice is provided by [[yumemi nemu (dempagumi)|Yumemi Nemu]], a model, actress, DJ, and singer from Dempagumi.inc. 

h4. See also

title: final_fantasy_vii
body:
The seventh JRPG developed by Squaresoft (now [[Square Enix]]) in the [[Final Fantasy]] series, and arguably the most popular game in the series. First released on the Sony [[PlayStation 1|PlayStation]] in 31 January 1997 (after a 3-year hiatus), and then re-released for personal computers in 1998.

The story is about Avalanche, an ecoterrorist organization combating the conglomerate Shinra Electric Power Company which is destroying the world's ecosystem by extracting mako for electricity. One of their latest recruits is acerbic mercenary [[Cloud Strife]], himself a former member of SOLDIER, Shinra's mako-enhanced supersoldier corps. Soon, however, Avalanche would face an even greater enemy in the form of [[Sephiroth]], another former SOLDIER intent on absorbing the planet's power and becoming a god.

A remake, aptly titled [[Final Fantasy VII Remake]], was announced at Sony's 2015 E3 conference. The remake is a multi-game series, the first installment of which was released in April 2020. It would be followed up by [[Final Fantasy VII Rebirth]] in February 2024.

title: adachi_to_shimamura
body:
A light novel series by Iruma Hitoma (å…¥é–“äººé–“) that centers around the friendship between two high-school girls, [[Adachi Sakura|Adachi]] and [[Shimamura Hougetsu|Shimamura]]. The story outlines their everyday events and contains mild [[yuri]] themes. It began as a series in Vol. 28 of é›»æ’ƒæ–‡åº«MAGAZINE (Dengeki Bunko Magazine) in March 2013. Since then, ten volumes have been published by ASCII Media Works with [[Ousaka Nozomi|Non]] (ã®ã‚“) as the illustrator.

There are two manga adaptions; a 3 volume 2013 one illustrated by [b]Mani[/b], which was serialized online via Square Enix's Gangan Online website, and the other, an ongoing adaptation that began in 2019 with illustrations by [[Yuzuhara moke]]. There is also a 12 episode anime adaption by [i]Tezuka Productions[/i] which aired Fall of 2020.

title: mizuhashi_parsee
body:
The "Jealousy Beneath the Crust of the Earth".

Stage 2 boss of [[Touhou]]'s [[Subterranean Animism]] and a side character in [[Foul Detective Satori]]. A Persian "Hashihime":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hashihime that has the ability to manipulate jealousy. She lives in the [[bridge]] leading to the underworld, often attempting to drive away anyone who attempts to cross it and losing herself in a jealous rage whenever she fails. Parsee also demonstrates the ability to have a [[clone|copy of herself]] through her spell cards. Often paired with [[Hoshiguma Yuugi]] or [[Kurodani Yamame]] in fanworks due to their stages being next to each other, but also [[Kagiyama Hina]] due to both being stage 2 bosses who deal with negative emotions. 


h4. Appearance
* !asset #23207809

Her appearance is very inconsistent and confusing, leading artists to draw her in a variety of ways. She usually has [[short hair|short]] [[blonde hair]] with a [[half updo]] or a [[half up braid]], [[green eyes]], [[pointy ears]]. Her outfit is a [[white scarf]], and then a [[short sleeves|short-sleeved]] [[brown shirt]] over a [[black dress]] but sometimes a separate [[black shirt|black]] [[undershirt]] and [[black skirt|skirt]], a [[white sash]], [[arm warmers]], [[loose socks|loose]] [[white socks]], and [[black footwear|black]] [[mary janes]].

h4. See also

* [[paru paru]]: An onomatopoeia for her jealousy
* [[Puru-see (hoshizuki (seigetsu))|Puru-see]]
* "Parsee the Green-eyed Grinch":[/pools/19590]

h4. External links

* "Touhou Wiki: Parsee Mizuhashi":http://en.touhouwiki.net/wiki/Parsee_Mizuhashi

title: the_end_(sonic_frontiers)
body:
The final boss of [[Sonic Frontiers]]. The End is the being responsible of destroying the Ancients' home planet, forcing them to flee towards Earth. After it followed them, the Ancients built four Titans to fight it, then seal it inside Cyber Space, a digital dimension. Many ages later, it tricks [[sonic_the_hedgehog|Sonic]] into liberating it once again, corrupting him in the process.

The End appears before [[Super Sonic]] and [[sage_(sonic)|Sage]] as a [[purple moon|purple]] [[moon]]. On Easy and Normal difficulties, the fight takes place in a quick-time event. On Hard difficulty, Sage must first face it in a shooting section while piloting [[supreme_(sonic_frontiers)|Supreme]].

In the game's Another Story campaign, added in [[sonic_frontiers_the_final_horizon|The Final Horizon]] update, The End will instead take control of Supreme and use it to fight Sonic, who uses the power unlocked from his corruption to grant his transformation a power boost and destroy it.

title: supreme_(sonic_frontiers)
body:
The fourth and last Titan faced by [[Super Sonic]] in [[Sonic Frontiers]]. A large, humanoid entity that wields an [[arm cannon]]. It has a predominantly white and red color scheme, unlike the other Titans' black and grey.

After the battle, Supreme is operated by [[sage_(sonic)|Sage]] to aid [[sonic_the_hedgehog|Sonic]] on a last stand against [[the_end_(sonic_frontiers)|The End]], a creature weakened and sealed by the Titans ages ago.

In the game's Another Story campaign, added in [[sonic_frontiers_the_final_horizon|The Final Horizon]] update, instead of fighting alone, the End will connect itself to the Titan, making it grow [[extra arms]] and walk on all fours. [[Super Sonic 2|Super Sonic]] must then sever their connection and use his corruption's power to destroy them.

title: mega_mawile
body:
The [[mega pokemon|Mega-Evolved]] form of [[Mawile]].

Type: Steel/Fairy
Ability: Huge Power
Height: 100 cm / 3'3"
Weight: 23.5 kg / 51.8 lbs

Mega Mawile looks similar to its non Mega-Evolved form, except it has pink colorations and markings on its body (while the markings on its head stay black). It grows over a foot (0.4 meters) in height, becomes more bulky in appearance, and grows a second jaw on its head (with both jaws becoming curved and jagged). In battle, this gives it the ability [b]Huge Power[/b], which effectively (with the slight boost to it base attack from Mega Evolving) gives it the highest attack stat in the entire game. This, along with its Fairy typing, has spawned a multitude of jokes, stating that Mawile is not only a Dragon slayer, but a world destroyer as well.

title: harukado_yua
body:
Female main character of [[Yoshibari Aubade]]. 

She is a second year student of senior high school. Yua belongs to the Rhythmic Gymnastics Club of the private Sakakigahara Academy and is one of the "Seven Deadly Sins" in that school, representing "Lust".
Often a victim of [[ryona]] and or [[humiliation]] by her enemies/rivals.

She has been close friends with Haruomi since childhood, but due to a past incident, they limit their closeness to within the home.
After being bitten by a newly transformed vampire Haruomi, she became a failed blood relative, a zombie, and is bound with ropes to suppress her outbursts.

In the sequel novel of [[Yoshibari Aubade]] called "Yoshibari Extra", Yua adopts the identity of the justice heroine "Muse Mask" as part of an undercover mission, wearing an extremely [[revealing clothes|revealing]] and obscene costume. This costume is heavily inspired by [[kekkou_kamen|Kekkou Kamen]], due to its excessive exposure and especially the full head [[mask]].

She also makes an appearance in [[Goddess_defeat:_reincarnation_valanowas|Goddess Defeat: Reincarnation Valanowas]] [å¥³ç¥æ•—åŒ— è»¢ç”Ÿã®ãƒ´ã‚¡ãƒ©ãƒãƒ¯] as a supporting character.

title: kali_(fate)
body:
Alter Ego-class Servant first debuting in [[Fate/Grand Order]]. One of the two major avatars of the [[Hindu mythology|Hindu]] mother goddess [[Parvati (fate)|]], alongside [[Durga (fate)|]] (represented by her first and second ascension). This form represents Parvati as the "goddess of destruction" and patron goddess of the Durga sect of Hinduism, which participated in various kinds of dark magic and esoteric sacrificial/sexual worshipping. As with her base form, she uses [[Matou Sakura]] as her vessel.

Designed by [[starshadowmagician]] and voiced by [[Shitaya Noriko]].

Need for Speed (NFS) is a racing video game franchise published by [[Electronic Arts]]. The first four games in the series were retitled as [b]Over Drivin'[/b] in Japan, before switching to the NFS branding.

The series centers around illicit street racing and in general tasks players to complete various types of races while evading the local law enforcement in police pursuits.

title: nolan_grayson
body: Nolan Grayson is a fictional character in the Image Universe, created by writer Robert Kirkman and artist Cory Walker (with Ryan Ottley) as an expansion of a character concept created by Alan Moore and Chris Sprouse. Omni-Man is the father of [[mark grayson|Invincible]] and Oliver Grayson, and a member of the alien Viltrumite race, working as a superhero on Earth. Omni-Man appears in Supreme, Invincible, Noble Causes, and Dynamo 5.

title: karen_mccormick
body: Character from [[South Park]], Karen McCormick is the youngest member of the McCormick family. She first appears as a background character in "Best Friends Forever". She later appeared in "The Poor Kid", where she played her first major role. Kenny is very protective of her, using his identity, Mysterion, to comfort her in hard times and keep her out of danger. Kenny's protectiveness as Mysterion extends to such a degree that she considers him her "guardian angel".

title: wendy_testaburger
body: Wendy Testaburger is a major-supporting character and the most prominent female character on [[South Park]]. She is the most prominent of the female classmates of [[stan marsh|Stan]], Kyle, Cartman, and Kenny, as well as Stan's on-and-off girlfriend. Wendy is a female fourth-grade student at South Park Elementary. She made her official first appearance and first official speaking role in the Season One episode "Cartman Gets an Anal Probe". Wendy has been voiced by four people during the series' run: Mary Kay Bergman, Mona Marshall, Eliza J. Schneider and currently April Stewart.

title: kurapika
body:
One of the main characters from [[Hunter x Hunter]].

A Blacklist Hunter and member of the Kurta Clan, being the only remaining member so far, Kurapika vows to avenge his fallen clan by destroying the Phantom Troupe after the latter massacred his clan for their "Scarlet Eyes", thus being his ultimate goal in becoming a Hunter.

He is usually calm, smart, and reticent, but becomes more wrathful and callous when threatened, attributing to his tragic past. This makes him impulsive sometimes, despite doing so for the sake of protecting his friends and avenging his clan.

Voiced by [[Hidaka Noriko]] (Pilot OVA), [[Kaida Yuki]] (1999), [[Sawashiro Miyuki]] (2011), and [[Erika Harlacher]] (2011; EN).

h4.Appearance
Kurapika has an [[androgynous]] appearance. He is a short [[blonde hair|blonde haired]] young man with [[brown eyes]] which turn [[red eyes|scarlet red]] in some occasions. His outfit is usually a [[tabard]] with reddish hem and a white [[white shirt|shirt]] and [[white pants|pants]]. His footwear is a blue-colored [[flats]].

title: beast_boy_(dc)
body: Beast Boy (Garfield Mark "Gar" Logan) is a superhero appearing in American comic books published by [[DC Comics]]. He has also gone under the alias Changeling. Created by writer Arnold Drake and artist Bob Brown, he is a shapeshifter who possesses the ability to transform into any animal he chooses. The character first appeared in Doom Patrol #99 (November 1965) and is usually depicted as a member of the Doom Patrol and the [[Teen Titans]].

title: ganesha_(mythology)
body:
In [[Hindu mythology]], [b]Ganesha[/b] (or [b]Ganesh[/b]) is the [[elephant]]-headed god of arts, knowledge, and willpower. He is one of the most well-known Hindi gods and is widely worshipped in several Hindu sects. In most traditions, Ganesha is the son of [[Shiva (mythology)|]] and [[Parvati (mythology)|]].

In most traditions, the story of how Ganesha got his elephant head usually revolves around how his father Shiva accidentally beheaded him either by his earth-scorching third eye or his [[chakram]] and used an elephant's head as a replacement. Another story says that Shiva found Ganesha too alluring, so he gave him an elephant head and [[fat|large belly]] to prevent future trouble.

title: close-quarters_combat
body:
[b]CQC[/b] ([b]Close-Quarters Combat[/b]) is a system of combined combat techniques which allow rapid alternation between armed and hand-to-hand combat while engaging enemy personnel. 

In the typical CQC stance, the user holds their [[gun]] (a one handed weapon such as a [[handgun]]) with their dominant hand while supporting it with the other hand, which holds their CQC [[knife]]. By using this stance, the gun remains steady for accurate engagement of opponents outside the range of unarmed combat, while allowing a quick transition to the knife for close-work. 

In the [[metal gear solid|Metal Gear Solid universe]] it's a style of close combat techniques developed together by [[The Boss]] and [[Big Boss]] of [[Metal Gear Solid 3: Snake Eater]]. 


Use this tag for when a character in the picture is wielding a gun and a knife.

h4. See also

* [[Dual wielding]]

title: basic_instinct_(movie)
body: A 1992 neo-noir, erotic thriller Western film directed by Paul Verhoeven. It follows police detective Nick Curran (played by Michael Douglas) on a serial murder case, who gets sexually involved with the prime suspect, Catherine Tramell (played by Sharon Stone), a cunning and manipulative author. The film is famous and infamous for its overt depictions of sex and violence, which were highly explicit for its time. It's most famous for its interrogation scene, in which Tramell intentionally flashes herself while switching [[crossed legs]] in her seat.

A Sargon tribal warrior from the jungle of Acahualla, she joined Rhodes Island on [[Blaze (arknights)|]]'s recommendation.

She comes from a Liberi tribe of smaller stature and frailer constitution, as such she wants to challenge stronger people in order to mold and improve herself, until she can beat them with her [[boxing gloves]].

She likes lushly colored flowers and gives a hand at [[Perfumer (arknights)|]]'s greenhouse.

Her motif is based on the white-necked jacobin.

title: taoist_rope
body:
The "Daoist/Taoist":[/wiki_pages/taoism] robe (é“è¢) is a traditional garment worn by Daoist practitioners, symbolizing their spiritual beliefs and cultural heritage. These robes are typically long and flowing, crafted from silk or cotton, and often adorned with symbols such as the "Eight Trigrams (bagua, å…«å¦)":[/wiki_pages/bagua] or "Yin-Yang (é˜´é˜³)":[/wiki_pages/yin_yang] to reflect Daoist philosophy. Designed for both ritual and daily use, they emphasize simplicity, harmony, and the connection between humans and nature, key tenets of Daoism. The robes vary in color and design, with different styles signifying the wearer's role, sect, or spiritual attainment.

h4. See also

* [[Taoism]]

title: shiki_eiki
body:
The "Highest Judge of Paradise", final boss and a playable character of [[Touhou]]'s [[Phantasmagoria of Flower View]].

A "yama":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yama responsible for judging the souls of the dead, having the ability to identify good and evil. She is best known, however, for being quite moralistic and calling out other characters on their faults - more so (sometimes with physical punishment) upon her errant shinigami, [[Onozuka Komachi]]. Based on her illustration from "The Grimoire of Marisa", fanworks often comically depict her as rather petite and [[flat chest|flat-chested]] compared to her imposing, busty employee - something which angers Eiki - though a full-figured woman with long legs and [[zettai ryouiki]] is another depiction often used in fanart. Canon is inconsistent on which form is true, with some speculation that the child depiction is used as an alternate form for reasons unknown.

Yamaxanadu (ãƒ¤ãƒã‚¶ãƒŠãƒ‰ã‚¥) is her title (meaning "Yama of Paradise"), but has led fans to erroneously read her name as "Shikieiki Yamaxanadu". In actuality, her given name is Eiki and her surname is Shiki.

h4. Appearance 
* !asset #24008538
* !asset #24008536: Grimoire of Marisa

She has [[short hair|short]] [[green hair]] often cut [[asymmetrical hair|asymmetrically]] and either [[blue eyes|blue]] or [[green eyes]]. Her outfit is a [[frilled hat|frilled]] [[blue hat]], a [[blue vest]] with [[buttons]] and a [[ribbon-trimmed vest|ribbon trim]] and [[epaulettes]], a [[white shirt]] with [[red bow|red]] and [[white bow]]s [[sleeve bow|on]] its [[long sleeves|sleeves]], a [[black skirt]] also with a [[ribbon-trimmed skirt|ribbon trim]], [[white socks]], and [[black footwear|black]] [[mary janes]]. She is often seen [[holding]] her [[rod of remorse]] or a red [[spider lily]].

h4. See also

* [[Enma (mythology)]]

h4. External links

* "Touhou Wiki: Eiki Shiki, Yamaxanadu":http://en.touhouwiki.net/wiki/Eiki_Shiki,_Yamaxanadu

title: mirko
body:
A character from [[Boku no Hero Academia]]. A professional hero with "rabbit" quirk, granting her various rabbit-like abilities such as immensely strong legs, capable of jumping at a great height, and superhuman hearing ability. Her civilian name is [b]Usagiyama Rumi[/b]. 

She is depicted as a [[dark skin|dark skinned]] or [[tan|tanned]], [[toned|athletic]] [[rabbit girl]] (albeit her fanart frequently depicted her with [[muscular female|muscular]] body instead) with [[white hair|white]], [[long hair]]. While under hero duties, she wear a [[white leotard]], which when combined with her organic rabbit ears and tail can make it appears as if she's wearing a playboy bunny outfit.

Mirko was named after Mirko "Cro Cop" Filipovich, a now retired [[mixed martial arts]] fighter and Kickboxer, best known for competing in [[Pride Fighting Championships]] and the [[Ultimate Fighting Championship]].

Due to a localization error, "Mirko" is sometimes inappropriately spelled as "Miruko". When he was fighting in Japan, "Mirko" had to be translated as "Miruko/ãƒŸãƒ«ã‚³" as Japanese does not have an independent "R" sound (the kanji ã‚‰ã‚Šã‚‹ã‚Œã‚ are roughly pronounced ra-ri-ru-re-ro). Western manga translators who did not know the reference unintentionally retranslated the faulty original translation.

title: forsaken_(world_of_warcraft)
body:
Forsaken is a Playable race of World of Warcraft.

The features of the dead resurrected as Forsaken are mainly reflected in their [[pale skin]] and uniformly [[yellow_eyes|yellow pupils]].

The Forsaken are a type of undead race, different from the Scourge and the Ebon Blade. They have the same emotions and willpower as they did in life.

They once served [[sylvanas_windrunner|Sylvanas]], and now they serve [[calia_menethil|Menethil]].

This race belongs to the [[horde_(world_of_warcraft)|Horde]] faction.

External Link:

title: chris_(konosuba)
body:
[b]Chris[/b] is a female character in the [[Kono Subarashii Sekai ni Shukufuku wo!|KonoSuba]] series. She is a thief and a member of the Eris Church who teaches [[satou_kazuma|Kazuma]] many thief skills and was [[darkness_(konosuba)|Darkness's]] first adventuring companion. She is a good friend of both Darkness and Kazuma.

Chris is a teenage girl with a light complexion and [[purple eyes]]. She has [[short hair|short]] [[grey hair|silver/grey hair]] and two strands of hair ([[sidelocks]]) framing her face with a piece of hair pointing out from her fringe ([[side ahoge]]). She also has a [[scar on cheek|scar]] on her right cheek. Most likely due to her tomboyish and outgoing nature, along with her [[small breasts|small]] (almost [[flat chest|flat]]) chest and short hair, she is often mistaken for a boy.

Chris usually wears a fairly revealing outfit. Her outfit consists of a light blue ([[aqua scarf|aqua]]) [[scarf]], a short [[green cape]] which goes down to her elbows, a pair of [[black gloves|black]] [[elbow gloves]] with normal [[brown gloves]] layered over them, [[short shorts|short]] [[denim shorts|blue jean-shorts]], [[white thighhighs]] with a [[blue trim|blue trimming]], [[brown footwear|brown]] [[boots]], and a bikini-like grey [[crop top|top]]. [spoiler]Ever since her first run-in with Kazuma, Chris has worn [[black leggings]] in case her [[panties]] are stolen again.[/spoiler] She also wears diamond-shaped blue [[earrings]] and usually has an enchanted [[dagger]] fastened to her waist on her back.

[spoiler]She is, in truth, the goddess [[eris_(konosuba)|Eris]] in mortal disguise.[/spoiler]

title: eric_cartman
body: Eric Theodore Cartman, commonly referred to as just Cartman, is a fictional character in the adult animated sitcom [[South Park]], created by Trey Parker and Matt Stone. He is voiced by Parker, and is one of the series' four main characters, alongside [[Stan Marsh]], [[Kyle Broflovski]], and [[Kenny McCormick]]. He first appeared with the name Kenny in the short film The Spirit of Christmas (1992), and later appeared in the 1995 film of the same title before debuting in "Cartman Gets an Anal Probe", the first episode of the series, on August 13, 1997.

title: kyle_broflovski
body: Kyle Broflovski is a fictional character in the adult animated sitcom [[South Park]]. He is voiced by and loosely based on series co-creator Matt Stone. Kyle is one of the series' four central characters, along with his friends [[Stan Marsh]], [[Kenny McCormick]], and [[Eric Cartman]]. He debuted on television when South Park first aired on August 13, 1997, after having first appeared in The Spirit of Christmas shorts created by Stone and long-time collaborator Trey Parker in 1992 (Jesus vs. Frosty) and 1995 (Jesus vs. Santa).

title: stan_marsh
body: Stanley "Stan" Marsh is a fictional character in the adult animated television series [[South Park]]. He is voiced by and loosely based on series co-creator Trey Parker. Stan is one of the series' four central characters, along with [[Kyle Broflovski]], [[Eric Cartman]], and [[Kenny McCormick]]. He debuted on television when South Park first aired on August 13, 1997, after having first appeared in The Spirit of Christmas shorts created by Parker and long-time collaborator Matt Stone in 1992 (Jesus vs. Frosty) and 1995 (Jesus vs. Santa).

title: chef_(south_park)
body: Chef Jerome McElroy, often referred to as just "Chef", is a fictional character on the Comedy Central series [[South Park]] who was voiced by Isaac Hayes. A cafeteria worker at the local elementary school in the town of South Park, Colorado, Chef is generally portrayed as more intelligent than the other adult residents of the town, and understanding to the children. His advice is often sought by the show's core group of child protagonists â€”[[Stan Marsh]], [[Kyle Broflovski]], [[Eric Cartman]], and [[Kenny McCormick]] â€” as he is the only adult they completely trust. He frequently gives completely honest advice without considering whether it is appropriate for children, usually in the non sequitur form of a lascivious soul song.

title: bebe_stevens
body: Bebe Stevens is [[South Park]] character, she first appears in "Cartman Gets an Anal Probe". She briefly became part of the boys' group in "Bebe's Boobs Destroy Society", but only because of her early developed breasts.

title: richard_wagner
body: Wilhelm Richard Wagner was a [[germany|German]] composer, theatre director, essayist, and conductor who is chiefly known for his operas.

title: johann_sebastian_bach
body: Johann Sebastian Bach (31 March [O.S. 21 March] 1685 â€“ 28 July 1750) was a [[germany|German]] composer and musician of the late Baroque period. He is known for his prolific output across a variety of instruments and forms, including orchestral music such as the Brandenburg Concertos; solo instrumental works such as the cello suites and sonatas and partitas for solo violin; keyboard works such as the Goldberg Variations and The Well-Tempered Clavier; organ works such as the Schubler Chorales and the Toccata and Fugue in D minor; and choral works such as the St Matthew Passion and the Mass in B minor. Since the 19th century Bach Revival, he has been generally regarded as one of the greatest composers in the history of Western music.

title: alex_delarge
body:
Protagonist of the novel and movie [[a_clockwork_orange|A Clockwork Orange]].
He loves violence, rape and classical music (that of [[Ludwig van Beethoven]] above all), and peppers his phrases with a made-up slang called Nadsat. He couldn't care any less about the consequences of his behavior... until they start catching up to him after a while, in much unpleasant ways for him.

title: a_clockwork_orange
body:
A 1971 crime film directed by [[Stanley Kubrick]]. Based on the 1962 novel of the same name.
It employs disturbing and violent themes to comment on psychiatry, juvenile delinquency, youth gangs, and other social, political, and economic subjects in a dystopian near-future Britain.

title: tie_bomber
body: The TIE/sa bomber, formally known as the TIE Surface Assault Bomber and also known as the TIE/sa tactical bomber or simply the TIE bomber, was a bombing variant of the TIE fighter series used by the Galactic Empire in the [[Star Wars]] series. An evolution of the TIE/gt, the TIE bomber was their main source of anti-emplacement air-support. They were nicknamed "dupes" by the New Republic pilot Wyl Lark.

title: spider-man_(2099)
body: Spider-Man 2099 is a superhero appearing in American comic books published by [[marvel|Marvel Comics]]. The character was created by Peter David and Rick Leonardi in 1992 for the Marvel 2099 comic book line, and he is a futuristic re-imagining of the original [[Spider-Man]] created by Stan Lee and Steve Ditko. His true identity is Miguel O'Hara, an Irish-Mexican geneticist living in Nueva York (a renamed New York City) in the year 2099 who attempts to re-create the abilities of the original Spider-Man in other people and later suffers a related accident that causes half of his DNA to be rewritten with a spider's genetic code.

title: guatemala
body: Guatemala, officially the Republic of Guatemala, is a country in Central America. It is bordered to the north and west by [[Mexico]], to the northeast by Belize, to the east by Honduras, and to the southeast by El Salvador. It is hydrologically bordered to the south by the Pacific Ocean and to the northeast by the Gulf of Honduras.

title: travis_grady
body:
The protagonist of [[Silent Hill: Origins]], the fifth installment in the [[Silent Hill (series)|]] series.
He is a troubled and lonely truck driver with a dark past. Travis is running late on a delivery to Brahms and decides to take a shortcut through the town of Silent Hill. In doing so, he remembers the horrible tragedies that took place years ago, as well as digging into a religious conspiracy regarding a cult known as the Order occurring within the town.

title: god_(silent_hill_3)
body: The god, also simply called God, is the final boss of [[Silent Hill 3]], encountered at the end of the chapel. She is the result of a partly-failed ritual to resurrect the deity of the town's religion.

title: numb_body_(silent_hill)
body: Numb Body is a monster from [[Silent Hill 3]]. They also appear in Silent Hill: The Arcade and the comics Dying Inside and Hunger.

title: douglas_cartland
body: Douglas Cartland is a character appearing in [[Silent Hill 3]]. He is a middle-aged private detective who was hired by Claudia Wolf, a cult leader, to locate [[Heather Mason]] and bring her to Silent Hill.

title: silent_hill_1
body: Silent Hill is a 1999 survival horror game developed by Team Silent, a group within Konami Computer Entertainment Tokyo, and published by Konami. As the first installment in the [[silent hill (series)|Silent Hill]] video game series, the game was released exclusively for the PlayStation. Silent Hill uses a third-person view with real-time rendering of 3D environments. To mitigate the limitations of the console hardware, developers used fog and darkness to obscure the graphics and hide pop-ins, which, in turn, helped establish the game's atmosphere and mystery. Unlike earlier survival horror games that focused on protagonists with combat training, the player character of Silent Hill is an "everyman".

title: bright_noa
body:
A fictional character from the [[Gundam]] [[mecha]]verse.

[b]Bright Noa[/b] was first introduced in [[Mobile Suit Gundam]] (1979). He is a skilled [[Earth Federation]]/[[AEUG]]/[[earth_federation_space_forces|Londo Bell]] captain who commands many [[space]] battleships, notably the [[White Base]] and the [[Argama]]. A meme ([[Bright Slap]]) sprung up from the way he literally [[slapping|slaps]] some sense into his subordinates, notably [[Amuro Ray]].

Has appeared in many U.C. series and anime like [[Zeta Gundam]] (1985), [[Gundam ZZ]] (1986), [[Char's Counterattack]] (1988) and [[Gundam Unicorn]] (2010).

Father of [[Hathaway Noa]] and [[Cheimin Noa]]. [spoilers]Husband of [[Mirai Yashima]][/spoilers]

title: darude_-_sandstorm_(meme)
body: A trance song by Finnish DJ Darude. Released in 1999, it is commonly used in sporting events and video game live streams to hype up the audience. It is also used for [[trolling]], where any question about the name of a song currently playing would be answered as "Darude â€“ Sandstorm", sometimes with a link to the official music video.

body:
Real name: [[James Rolfe]]

An American internet celebrity, known for his series of videos where he is a [[otaku|video game nerd]] that reviews poor-quality video games, usually [[NES]] games from the late 1980's, as well as other consoles like [[Atari 2600]], [b]Sega Genesis[/b]/[[Sega Mega Drive]], [[Super Famicom]]/[[Super Nintendo]], etc. He has roasted to great lengths many mediocre games made by [[LJN]].

title: nasu_kinoko
body:
Nasu Kinoko (real name [b]Nasu Kunihiro[/b]) (born 28 November 1973) is a Japanese author, best known for writing the visual novels [[Tsukihime]] and [[Fate/stay night]]. Renowned for a unique style of storytelling and prose, Nasu is amongst the most prominent visual novelists in Japan.

For Danbooru purposes, this tag is referring to the [[Toad (mario)|]]-like [[artist self-insert]].

h4. See also

* Home page: http://www.remus.dti.ne.jp/~takeucto/

title: chibikemo
body:
A genre of popular [[furry]] character in Japan, literally being an abbreviation of [[chibi]] and [[furry|kemono]].

[b]Not all chibi furries are chibikemo[/b] - chibikemo characters are designed with very small proportions even by chibi standards, usually fitting into the archetype of "TDM" (a [[mascot]] character who is 2-3 heads tall).

Chibikemo characters often have big eyes, are primarily animal-shaped despite their bipedal stance and anthropomorphic behavior (often being [[digitigrade]]), and are frequently fantasy [[creature]]s.

[[Chibi]] itself might not always apply, depending on the proportions of the character.

h4. Examples

* !post #8281044
* !post #8246509

h4. See also

* [[chibi]]
* [[deformed]]
* [[mini person]]

title: ultraman_tarou
body:
The titular Ultra of [[Ultraman Tarou (series)|]]. His [spoiler]former[/spoiler] human host is [[Higashi Kotaro]].

He's also the son of both [[Mother of Ultra]] and [[Father of Ultra]], despite resembling his cousin, [[Ultraseven]].

He also has a powered up form known as [b]Super Ultraman Tarou[/b], which he achieves by merging with [[Ultraman]], [[Zoffy (ultra series)|]], Ultraseven, [[Ultraman Jack]], and [[Ultraman Ace]], the first instance of 'Ultra Overlapping' (fusion) in the series, turning him into a Super Ultra. He looks visually the same, with the exception of his body glowing with glitter at times.

h4. Appearance

* !post #503188

h4. External links

* "Wikipedia: Ultraman Taro":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ultraman_Taro_(character)

title: ultraman_jack
body:
The 'titular' Ultra of [[Kaette Kita Ultraman]]. He was only referred to as Ultraman in the original series, prompting the need for a new name in follow-up appearances. He would adopt several temporary names, such as [i]Kaeriman[/i] ("Returned Man", derived from the series title), [i]Shinman[/i] ("New Man", shortened from [i]Shin Ultraman[/i]) and [i]Ultraman II[/i], before finally settling upon Ultraman Jack by 1984.

h4. Appearance

* !post #886969: Jack on the far right

h4. See also

* [[Ultra Bracelet]]

h4. External links

* "Wikipedia: Ultraman Jack":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ultraman_Jack_(character)

title: mandoline_(utensil)
body:
A cooking utensil used to [[slicing|slice]] vegetables or fruits, consists of a flat board with blade(s) attached.

Not to be confused with [[grater]]. The differences being that grater has holes as blades while mandoline's blades usually don't take up most of the surface of the untensil like a grater.

title: kakania_(reverse:1999)
body:
[b]Kakania[/b] is a playable character in [[Reverse:1999]]. She is an Unlicensed Psychiatrist in Vienna that often do her practices in secret. She have an ability to project someone's inner thought into a mirror, that play a big part not only in her job, but also in the story. She is the friend of [[Isolde (Reverse:1999)|]].

She is voiced by Aiden Dawn in English and [[Saitou Chiwa]] in Japanese.

h4. Appearance
* !post #7662694: Default
* !post #7662695: Insight II: Reflections within Reflections
* !post #8524460: [[Kakania (Seminars on Serenity) (Reverse:1999)|Seminars on Serenity]]

title: shaved_ice
body:
A Japanese [[dessert]] consisting of shaved ice in a cup, flavored with syrup and a sweetener (often condensed milk), and eaten with a spoon.

Japanese shaved ice stands usually have a flag with the kanji "ice" on it called [[kooribata]].

title: rurima_(cookie)
body:
* !asset #21073385
* !asset #21073383

Voice of [[Hakurei Reimu]] in [[Atouda Ako (character)|]]'s [[cookie_(touhou)|Kusoâ˜†â˜†â˜†]]. Her extremely unique voice and realistic voice acting instantly made her one of Cookie's most popular characters and the breakout star of the entire Kuso series. Not of fan of the -aneki suffix to her name, so instead fans now call her Rurima-san. While initially accepting of the Cookie fame, she began to slowly get angrier with the fandom starting in 2017. Ended all of her accounts in 2021.

Identifiable by her [[long hair|long]] [[brown hair]] with [[blunt bangs]], her [[pink apron]] with her [[character name|name]] [[clothes writing|on it]], and [[holding_grater|holding]] a [[hand grater]] used to make [[carrot shirishiri]]. Her voice acting in many doujin and adult works made her associated with dirty jokes and [[ANNYUI (cookie)|]], especially her line about omanko. Was a massive fan of the [[Touken Ranbu]] character [[Heshikiri Hasebe]] and is now drawn with a [[katana]], with some psychopathic edge.

title: plopper_(the_simpsons)
body: Plopper the Pig is [[Homer Simpson|Homer Simpson's]] pet [[pig]] in [[The Simpsons]]. Homer first met Plopper when he and Bart were in Krusty Burger. Plopper is mostly famous for being called "Spider-Pig".

title: st._trina_(elden_ring)
body:
[b]Saint Trina[/b] is a character in [[Elden Ring]]. They were a mysterious figure associated with [[sleeping|sleep]] and [[dreaming|dream]] related items and objects.

In [[elden ring: shadow of the Erdtree|Shadow of the Erdtree]], [spoiler]she is confirmed to have been a [[dual persona]] of [[Miquella (elden ring)|]] - which was widely speculated beforehand.[/spoiler]

title: satella_(rance)
body:
Character in the [[Rance (series)|Rance Series]], introduced in [[Rance III]] as a major antagonist, before returning as an ally in later games.

A childhood friend of [[Hornet (Rance)|]] and a member of her faction, Satella is a cruel, but apathetic, Dark Lord who thinks lowly of humans, thinking of them like insects.

In Rance III and [[Rance 03|its remake]], she allies with [[Patton Misnarge]] of Helman, alongside her fellow Dark Lords [[Noce]] and [[Aizel]], to invade Leazas.

title: buran_(spacecraft)
body: The Soviet response to American space shuttles. A single working Buran spacecraft was built and flew one uncrewed mission back in 1988 before the project was canned due to the USSR collapse. The spacecraft itself was destroyed back in 2002 when the hangar it was housed in suffered a roof collapse.

title: melissa_kinrenka
body:
[b]Melissa Kinrenka[/b] is a former [[Nijisanji]] [[virtual YouTuber]]. 
Character designed anonymously. They graduated on 01 June 2022. 

h4. Appearance
[tn]See post #3770437.[/tn]

They have light [[green eyes]]. Their hair is [[very long hair|very long]] and colorful, consisting of [[white hair|white]], [[green hair|green]], [[blonde hair|yellow]], [[black hair|black]], and [[red hair|red]]. Although it's typically tied into [[twintails]], it isn't always.

h5. Default
While their shirt is [[white shirt|white]], it has what can only be described as a [[black dress]] covering parts of it. They have black [[short shorts]]. A [[black jacket]] hangs off of their arms and is rarely worn properly. Their shoes are black [[boots]].

A white [[single strap]] is slightly visible that is presumably attached to the shirt. From a glance, their shirt can easily be mistaken as being [[sleeveless]], a mistake many artist make.

h5. Alternate Outfits
When they reached 50,000 subscribers on YouTube, a new, much more simplistic outfit was featured. It's a [[grey hoodie]] with black [[striped sleeves|vertical stripes]] on their sleeves. A [[green trim]] is featured on the bottom of it and the inner-color is [[pink hoodie|pink]].

Their [[pants]] are somewhat [[baggy]]. Half of them are [[grey pants|grey]], while the other half is [[black pants|black]]. Orange and green [[strap]]s wrap around either leg asymmetrically. 

This outfit features a black [[choker]] and [[white footwear|white shoes]] with [[orange socks]].

They wear two hairstyles with this outfit: a [[short hair|short]] style and a much [[very long hair|longer]] style worn [[hair down|down]].

title: godolphin_barb_(umamusume)
body:
In [i][[Umamusume]][/i], the Godolphin Barb refers both to one of the Three Goddesses of the [i]Umamusume[/i] universe as well as a training AI based on her, who is one of the hosts of the Grand Masters scenario. She represents "Love" and is represented by the color blue.

A [[horse girl]], she has [[long_hair|long]] [[blue hair]] and [[blue eyes]]. She wears a [[blue_jacket|blue]] [[track jacket]] and [[black shorts]] as well as [[ear covers]]. She has an accessory on [b]her right ear[/b].

She is based on the Godolphin Barb (or Arabian), one of the foundation sires of the Thoroughbred breed of horses. His umamusume's blue theme is likely based on the Godolphin stable's royal blue racing silks. Through Matchem, he is the sire-line ancestor of about 1% of all Thoroughbreds. Even of all that, the overwhelming majority of living descendants are through Man O' War. In the context of [i]Umamusume[/i], he only has [[Calstone Light O (umamusume)|]] as a real-life descendant. Otherwise, [[Oguri Cap (umamusume)|]] would come the closest as the real horse's damsire (Silver Shark) is also of that sire-line.

h5. Associated characters
[[Darley Arabian (Umamusume)|]] - Fellow Goddess/Training AI
[[Byerley Turk (Umamusume)|]] - Fellow Goddess/Training AI

title: izayoi_sakuya
body:
The "Perfect and Elegant Maid". Stage 5 boss of [[Touhou]]'s [[Embodiment of Scarlet Devil]] and later the third most recurring playable character (being playable in six official games) after protagonists [[Hakurei Reimu]] and [[Kirisame Marisa]].

Head [[maid]] of the [[Scarlet Devil Mansion]] and personal attendant to its mistress [[Remilia Scarlet]] despite being the only human in the household. Sakuya possesses mastery of [[throwing knife|throwing knives]], as well as the ability to slow and stop time, making her somewhat a homage to [[Dio Brando]] of [[JoJo no Kimyou na Bouken]]. She is zealously loyal to Remilia, and is frequently depicted in doujin berating the gatekeeper, [[Hong Meiling]], though their relationship in canon is generally much friendlier. Due to her [[Immaterial and Missing Power]] portrait depicting her with considerably larger breasts than her usual portraits, jokes abound of her using [[breast padding]].

h4. Example

* !post #7492203: Usual Appearance
* !post #5610852: Full Body

h4. Related Pools

* Pool #5086:  Touhou - Sakuya's Pads
* Pool #21411:  Touhou - Sakuya's Elegant Knives

h4. See also

* [[breast padding]]
* [[knifed]]
* [[Tsurikichi Obasan]]
* [[Inu Sakuya (nejikirio)|]]: a dog-like caricature of Sakuya, from [[Nejikirio]]'s work.

h4. External links

title: judgement_armor
body:
Judgement Armor or Judgment Armos is the tier 2 paladin armor set of [i]World of Warcraft[/i].

"The Judgement concept is meant to be an Inquisitor-like outfit. The Silver Hand is an overall noble establishment, to be sure -- but there is a time when pleasantries must end and justice must be done. It is called the Judgement armor for a reason -- it is the Paladin's embodiment of delivering their sentence upon the enemy. This is not the defender aspect of the Paladin you're seeing; it is the commanding, faceless aspect of justice, of judgement. There is more to a Paladin than shining armor."

â€”Blizzard Community Manager Caydiem

title: fox_mccloud
body:
The protagonist of the [[Star Fox]] franchise, and the leader of the titular mercenary team.

The son of the late [[James McCloud]], he is a fearless hero and an excellent pilot, with few being on par with his skills, such as his fellow pilot [[Falco Lombardi]] and arch-nemesis [[Wolf O'Donnell]].

He is playable in the [[Super Smash Bros.]] franchise, and is available as a fighter in all five games. He is also infamous for being the best character in [i]Melee[/i], to the point where he became memetic among the Smash community.

title: pablo_picasso_(person)
body:
[b]Pablo Diego JosÃ© Francisco de Paula Juan Nepomuceno MarÃ­a de los Remedios Cipriano de la SantÃ­sima Trinidad Ruiz y Picasso[/b] (1881-1973) was a [[spain|Spanish]] painter, sculptor, printmaker, ceramicist and theatre designer who spent most of his adult life in France.

 One of the most influential artists of the 20th century, he is known for co-founding the Cubist movement, the invention of constructed sculpture, the co-invention of collage, and for the wide variety of styles that he helped develop and explore.

title: takizakura_school_uniform
body:
The [[school uniform]] worn by students of Takizakura Girls' Academy in [[Love Live! School Idol Musical]].

The main [[winter uniform]] consists of a [[long sleeves|long-sleeved]] [[white shirt|white]] [[collared shirt|collared]] [[dress shirt]], a [[red jacket|red]] [[blazer]], a blue diagonal-striped [[necktie]] or [[bowtie]], and a [[brown skirt|brown]] [[plaid skirt|plaid]] [[skirt]]. Owing to the school's focus on modernity, the uniform's attributes can be freely swapped out or customized by students.

The [[summer uniform]] (shown in [[love live! school idol musical the drama|the drama adaptation]]) instead has a [[short sleeves|short-sleeved]] white shirt, no jacket, and a [[red skirt|red]] plaid skirt.

h4. See also
* [[Tsubakisakuhana school uniform]]

title: world_baseball_classic
body:
The [b]World Baseball Classic[/b] is a worldwide [[baseball]] tournament held every four years in March that pits twenty teams from different countries against each other in both pool and tournament play to determine a world champion.

Japan has the most WBC titles with three (2006, [[2009 World Baseball Classic|2009]] and [[2023 World Baseball Classic|2023]]), while the Dominican Republic (2013) and the United States (2017) are tied with one apiece.

h4. External links

title: baseball
body:
A bat-and-ball sport played between two teams of nine players. The aim is to score runs by hitting a thrown [[baseball (object)|ball]] with a [[baseball bat|bat]] and touching a series of four [[baseball base|bases]] arranged at the corners of a 90-foot diamond. 

Players on the batting team take turns hitting against the pitcher of the fielding team, which tries to stop them from scoring runs by getting hitters out in any of several ways. A player on the batting team can stop at any of the bases and later advance via a teammate's hit or other means. The teams switch between batting and fielding whenever the fielding team records three outs. One turn at bat for each team constitutes an inning and nine innings make up a professional game. The team with the most runs at the end of the game wins.

When referring to the ball and not the sport, use [[baseball (object)]].

title: alice_margatroid
body:
The "Seven-Colored Puppeteer".

[[Touhou]] character. Stage 3 and Extra Stage boss of [[Mystic Square]] and later a recurring playable character. One of the few [[touhou (pc-98)|PC-98 era]] characters (along with [[Hakurei Reimu|Reimu]] and [[Kirisame Marisa|Marisa]]) to reappear in the Windows-era games. She first appeared in her current design as the Stage 3 boss of [[Perfect Cherry Blossom]]. She is often accompanied by her dolls, [[Shanghai Doll]], [[Hourai Doll]], or [[Goliath Doll]].

A human-turned-youkai [[witch]] who specializes in manipulating [[doll]]s and using them to attack her enemies. Unlike [[Kirisame Marisa|Marisa]], her neighbor in the [[Forest of Magic]], Alice is not only rather aloof, but also somewhat cowardly at heart, refusing to use her full power for any reason because she would not know how to deal with losing. This nature leads to [[doujinshi]] portraying her as having some tendencies of being [[tsundere]] towards her [[human village (touhou)|human neighbor]]. Speculated to be the daughter of [[Shinki (touhou)|]]. Bearer of the [[Grimoire of Alice]].

h4. Appearance

* !post #7010229: Usual Appearance
* !post #2191177: [[Alice Margatroid (pc-98)|PC-98]][br]([[Mystic Square]])

She has [[short hair|short]] [[blonde hair]] with a [[frilled hairband|frilled]] [[red hairband]] and [[blue eyes]]. Her outfit is a [[pink neckerchief|pink]] or [[red neckerchief]], a [[white capelet]] over a (possibly) [[sleeveless dress|sleeveless]] [[blue dress]] and a [[long sleeves|long-sleeved]] [[white shirt]], a [[pink sash|pink]] or [[red sash]], and [[brown footwear|brown]] [[boots]].

title: swiss_guard
body:
The [b]Papal Swiss Guard[/b](also known as the Papal Guards) is an elite military unit from [[Switzerland]] that have protected the [[Pope]] since 1506. 

While the name "Swiss Guard" originally meant an elite bodyguard unit of Swiss soldiers that protected some European Monarchs in the past, today, the name now refers to the Papal Swiss Guard in Vatican City ever since Switzerland banned the practice of their citizens working in foreign armies since 1848 with the Vatican being an exception.

The Papal Swiss Guard are famous for their renaissance era uniforms and wielding halberds while on duty.  As their name reveals, only Swiss, Catholic males who are single, around the ages 19 to 30 and served in the Swiss Armed Forces may join the Papal Swiss Guard.

title: banzai_bill
body:
A larger version of a [[Bullet Bill]], known in Japanese as [i]Magnum Killer[/i]. Aside from the size, the common main differences is that the Banzai Bill has a visible mouth with [[sharp teeth]] and lacks arms.

Renamed in English as [b]Boomer Bill[/b] for the [[LEGO Super Mario]] [i]Boomer Bill Barrage Expansion Set[/i] in 2020, and renamed again as [b]Bomber Bill[/b] on the official [[Super Mario World]] website on the Mario Portal in 2022. The Bomber Bill rename is seemingly being kept for the foreseeable future, with its usage in the [[The Super Mario Bros. Movie]] in 2023 and [[Super Mario Party Jamboree]] in 2024.

title: forced_partners
body:
When two or more unwilling individuals are forced to participate in sexual acts with each other. 
This might be because of being [[bound together]] by restraints, being coerced, or because of being under (apparent) duress, such as being held [[at gunpoint]] or other [[threat]]s.

If any (but not all) of the participants [i]are[/i] willing, you should probably use the [[rape]] tag instead.
Avoid using this tag when the participants are merely under [[hypnosis]] or [[mind control]], unless their powerless "inner selves" are also portrayed witnessing the scene.

title: gyaru_v
body:
An upside-down [[V]] gesture.

The original term is called "Gyaru-peace", which is a combination of the Japanese pronunciation of "Gal," an English slang for women and girls, and the English word "Peace," which means finger gesture [[V]].

Originating from Japan's [[Gyaru]] culture, it is a hand gesture that first extends the arm forward and turns the palm up and down after making a V-shape by hand.

title: ice_age_(movie)
body:
An American franchise of animated movies revolving around animals of the titular period of time.
Five theatrical films have been released in the series: Ice Age in 2002, Ice Age: The Meltdown in 2006, Ice Age: Dawn of the Dinosaurs in 2009, Ice Age: Continental Drift in 2012, and Ice Age: Collision Course in 2016. title: ibuki_suika
body:
The "Little Pandemonium". Final boss of [[Touhou]]'s [[Immaterial and Missing Power]] and later a recurring playable character. 

Suika claims to be the only [[oni]] living above the ground in [[Gensokyo]] - the rest of her kind have lived underground for centuries. She is always found [[drunk]]en, carrying a bottomless [[gourd]] of [[sake]], and is an avid lover of parties. She has the power to control the density of any given object. She is explicitly based on the oni king Shuten-douji.

She is friends with [[Yakumo Yukari]], [[Hoshiguma Yuugi]] (both were once part of the "Four Devas of the Mountains") and [[Hakurei Reimu]], whose shrine also serves as her sometimes home. She and [[Ibaraki Kasen]] appear to have a slightly strained relationship, given Kasen's breaking rank with the other Gensokyo Sages, but the two remain mostly friendly to each other.

h4. Appearance
* !asset #24058201

Her hair color varies between [[blonde hair|blonde]], [[brown hair|brown]], or [[orange hair|orange]] but is almost always [[very long hair|very long]] and [[low-tied long hair|tied near the bottom]] with [[sidelocks]]. Her eyes also [[yellow eyes|vary]] [[brown eyes|between]] [[orange eyes|those]] colors or [[red eyes|red]]. She wears a [[red bow]] in her [[hair bow|hair]] and a [[purple bow]] [[horn bow|on]] [[brown horns]]. Her outfit is a [[sleeveless shirt|sleeveless]] [[white shirt]], a [[red bowtie]], a [[ribbon-trimmed skirt|ribbon-trimmed]] [[purple skirt]], [[white socks]], and [[black footwear|black]] [[shoes]]. She sometimes has her [[wrist cuffs]] or normal [[cuffs]] with a [[cube]], [[orb]], and [[pyramid (geometry)|]] attached on [[chain]]s. 

h4. See also

* [[List of Touhou characters]]

h4. External links

* "Touhou Wiki: Suika Ibuki":http://en.touhouwiki.net/wiki/Suika_Ibuki

body:
A [[strapless]] close-fitting casual [[dress]]. Essentially a [[tube top]] extended to dress length. Tube dresses generally reach from just past the hips to knee length, and they tend to fit snugly around the legs like a [[pencil skirt]] or [[pencil dress]].

As this tag implies [[strapless]], do not use this tag if the dress has shoulder straps or a [[halterneck]]; in such cases, [[pencil dress]] should be used instead.

body:
[[Hugh (pokemon)|]]'s unnamed younger sister from [[pokemon_bw2|PokÃ©mon BW2]]. She takes her appearance from the [[twins_(pokemon)|Twin]] NPC Trainer.
She was gifted a [[Purrloin]] by her late grandfather, but it was stolen by a member of the [[Shadow Triad]] a few years prior to the main story's events. title: sylveon
body:
[[Pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #700 in the National PokÃ©Dex. 

It evolves from [[Eevee]] when leveled up knowing a Fairy-type move and having at least two Affection hearts. The method of getting Affection has changed from game to game, since Generation 6. 

Sylveon is a quadruped, mammalian PokÃ©mon covered primarily in pale cream-colored fur with pinkish feet, ears, and tail. There are two [[bow]]s on its body, one on its left ear and one around its neck, from which two feelers adorn it. The bows are pale cream with pinkish centers, while the feelers are pale cream with pinkish and blue tips. It has short, slender legs and small paws with three visible toes on each foot. Its eyes are blue with white pupils and no visible sclera.

The shiny variant keeps the cream-colored fur, but replaces the pink fur with a minty blue color. The ribbons end with a pinkish color, and its eyes are red instead of blue. 

Japanese name: [b]Nymphia[/b]

Type: Fairy
Ability: Cute Charm (Hidden: Pixilate)
Height: 100 cm / 3'3"
Weight: 23.5 kg / 51.8 lbs

"Bulbapedia page":[https://bulbapedia.bulbagarden.net/wiki/Sylveon_(Pok%C3%A9mon)]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Aurorus]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Hawlucha]]

title: zoroark
body:
[[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] #571 in the National PokÃ©Dex, a Dark type PokÃ©mon.
Zoroark is a bipedal, gray-brown, fox-like PokÃ©mon with crimson and black accents. It has a pointed snout and ears with red insides. It also has some red rimming its eyes and mouth. It has a large, red, voluminous mane with black tips, which somewhat resembles a ponytail, as a teal bangle down its length separates a mass of the mane from the lower portion. It has a black ruff on its upper body, pointed at the shoulders from which its arms extend.

The first [[pokemon|PokÃ©mon]] to be revealed to appear in the fifth main installment of the PokÃ©mon franchise. The fox-like PokÃ©mon is a Dark-type that evolves from [[Zorua]]. It uses its Illusion ability [[disguised_zoroark|to disguise itself as other PokÃ©mon]]. A Zoroark took the central role in the thirteenth [[pokemon_(anime)|PokÃ©mon movie]].

It evolves from [[Zorua]].

Type: Dark
Ability: Illusion
Height: 160 cm / 5'3"
Weight: 81.1 kg / 178.8 lbs

Japanese Name: [b]Zoroark[/b]

Prior PokÃ©mon: [[Zorua]]
Next PokÃ©mon: [[Minccino]]

title: cheese
body:
A type of typically solid dairy products; mostly made from cow's milk (types from other animals exist), beaten and stirred until it has reached the right texture and softness.

It is typically used as a condiment for various meat-heavy [[food]], such as [[burger]] or [[pizza]], or as a topping for other snacks.

title: kite_shield
body: A type of tall medieval European [[shield]] with a distinctive pointed almond shape (hence also sometimes called an [i]almond shield[/i]). Commonly associated with the Battle of Hastings (1066) due to its ubiquity on the Bayeux tapestry. Not to be confused with a [i]heater shield[/i], which is the classic smaller point-at-the-bottom shield shape commonly seen in heraldry, early issues of [i][[Captain America]][/i], and United States Interstate Highway System signage.

title: scutum
body: The stereotypical [[shield]] of the ancient Roman [[legionnaire|legionary]], tall and usually rectangular, with a distinctive outward vertical curvature. The [i]scutum[/i] appeared among Romans in the fourth century BC, its precise origins unknown, and largely replaced the earlier [i]clipeus[/i], a circular shield adopted from the classical Greeks. Also often sported (in a wildly exaggerated form) by members of the [[Adeptus Astartes]] of [i][[warhammer 40k|Warhammer 40,000]], as part of their general faux-Roman styling.

title: planted_shield
body: When a [[shield]] is placed with its lower edge touching, or even driven into, the ground, converting it into a makeshift [[wall]]. For obvious reasons, this is more often done with large shields, such as medieval [[kite shield]]s or ancient Roman [i][[scutum|scuta]][/i].

title: agartha_(fate/grand_order)
body:
[b]Pseudo-Singularity II: Subterranean World of Folklore, Agartha[/b]
[quote]
The Demon God Pillars who were seperated from the 72 Demon Gods each found their purpose.
These scraps of the Beast scattered around the globe, forming Pseudo-Singularitiesâ€”stains in the fabric of human history.
Central Asia, the 21st century.
In a time and place where no major conflicts were recorded, a Singularity has appeared underground, and a Demon God Pillar's influence is suspected.
The next Pseudo-Singularity operation will take place in the vast subterranean cavern Agartha.
[/quote]
The second pseudo-singularity in [[Fate/Grand Order]], set in a massive underground world beneath the Asian continent in the year 2000. After the events of the [[Solomon (singularity) (fate/grand order)|Solomon singularity]], several [[demon pillar (fate)|]]s escaped and created subcategory singularities, resulting in the creation of Agartha (among others).

Released on the Japanese server on June 29, 2017 and on the NA server on June 21, 2019. It was adapted into a manga by [[Takenaka Hideo]].

Upon release of Agartha (and the other pseudo-singularities), the true name of several new servants was initially hidden; however official Fate/Grand Order media would later forego keeping their true names hidden in promotional materials. Their aliases are listed below, but their true names are used on Danbooru for tagging.

title: camelot_(fate/grand_order)
body:
[b]Sixth Singularity: Divine Realm of the Round Table, Camelot[/b]
[quote]
The setting of the sixth Grand Order is the year 1273, a holy land where many gather to worship.
Gallant knights battle for the restoration of humanity in a kingdom scarred by a history that should not exist!
[/quote]

The sixth singularity in [[Fate/Grand Order]]. Set in the year 1273 in [[Jerusalem]], it was originally registered as a variation of the Ninth Crusade that was successful in reaching Jerusalem; however due to the summoning of the [[Lion King (Lancer) (Fate)|Lion King]] it instead became home to a recreation of the city of Camelot from Arthurian legend, with the Chaldean forces arriving 6 months later.

Released on the Japanese server on July 25, 2016 and on the NA server on June 28, 2018. It was adapted into 2 anime films, [i]Wandering; Agateram[/i] and [i]Paladin; Agateram[/i].

title: fuyuki_(fate/grand_order)
body:
[b]Singularity F: Flame Contaminated City, Fuyuki[/b]
[quote]
Disaster strikes Chaldea, the Security Organization for the Preservation of Humanity.
A lone Master is thrown into Fuyuki during the year 2004, where a Holy Grail War is raging.
The journey to reclaim human history begins in a desolate, burning city.
[/quote]
The tutorial singularity in [[Fate/Grand Order]]. Technically the first singularity, but isn't numbered as such as it serves as a prologue, instead being known as Singularity F. It's set in the year 2004 in the Japanese town of Fuyuki, where a [[Fate/stay night|certain holy grail war]] has ended in disaster. It was adapted into the film [i][[Fate/Grand Order: First Order]][/i].

title: light_bulb_above_head
body:
A trope in which a [[light bulb]] appears over a character's head, usually after an extended period of [[thinking]]. It is a cartoony way of showing an [[idea]] switching on.

The light bulb should appear above the characters head and not be a background detail. Do not confuse for [[spoken light bulb]]s or a [[light_bulb_hair_ornament]]. 

* !post #8474129: Most classic positions are directly centered above the head

title: shinjou_akane
body:
The second female protagonist of [[SSSS.Gridman]].

[spoiler]She is revealed to be the series' secondary antagonist, working with [[Alexis Kerib]] by designing [[kaiju|kaiju]] sculptures that Alexis brings to life. Akane is shown to be sociopathic as she easily holds petty grudges against others, even for simple accidents.[/spoiler]

[spoiler]In episode 6, it is revealed that Akane is the creator of the city and uses the kaiju to shape it to her liking by killing off anyone she doesn't like and resetting it afterwards.[/spoiler]

[spoiler]In the finale episode, it is revealed that Akane is actually [[shinjou_akane_(real)|a person]] from [[real life]] world who was abducted by Alexis so he could feed on her negative energy.[/spoiler]

title: creeper
body:
A [[monster]] from the game [[Minecraft]]. It is one of the most dangerous hostile mobs in the game. Spawns in the Overworld on light level of zero. Its only attack is to [[explosion|explode]], fatally damaging the player, and destroying nearby blocks. This, combined with its nearly silent footsteps and its only making its trademark "Tsss" (or "ã‚·ãƒ¥ãƒ¼" as it's known in Japanese) when it is about to explodeâ€”has given it a notorious reputation for taking players completely by surprise.

Amongst the Japanese community it has earned the nickname "åŒ " or "ãŸãã¿ (Takumi)", which translates to "Craftsman." Being one of the most memorable and original mobs in the game, it has become a kind of mascot for Minecraft.

It is the primary source of gunpowder. A creeper surviving a lightning strike will turn into the more powerful [[charged creeper]]. If killed by a [[skeleton (minecraft)|]] or [[stray (minecraft)|]], it will drop a [[music disc (minecraft)|]].

h4.See also

title: hanuman_vs._7_ultraman
body:
a.k.a. "[i]The 6 Ultra Brothers vs. the Monster Army[/i]" in Japan.

A theatrical movie from the [[Ultra Series]], released in 1974 in Thailand, and in 1979 in Japan.

This movie is a international co-production between [[Tsuburaya Productions]] and Chaiyo Productions, a company from Thailand.

Nowadays, it is notorious for instigating the court battle between Tsuburaya and Chaiyo, over the international licensing rights for the Ultra Series, specifically, the first six entries, ([[Ultra Q]], [[Ultraman (1st series)|]], [[Ultraseven (series)|]], [[Kaette kita Ultraman|Return of Ultraman]], [[Ultraman Ace (series)|]], and [[Ultraman Tarou (series)|]]) of the franchise.

title: madou_meihou-sou_no_kousatsu
body:
[b]A Study in the Dubious Meihou-sou[/b]

[quote]The story begins when a new minute Singularity is detected...

Structured differently than any yet seen, the Singularity contains myriad locations and symbols from various time periods all in one place.
It's almost like like being in a movie.
In this world, created from the bitter frustration of a filmmaker who left a movie unfinished, completing the production is of the greatest importance.

Amid a flurry of speculation about the film's ending, one can only wonder how this story will conclude when the mystery is finally laid to rest.
[/quote]

An event in [[Fate/Grand Order]] guest-written by Madoi Ban which was later adapted into a novel illustrated by [[Honjou Raita]]. In it, Chaldea visits a singularity where they must finish the production of a murder-mystery themed film. [[Murasaki Shikibu (fate)|]] ends up penning the draft for the story, but the ending (and who the mastermind is) remains up in the air until production is concluded. This event also introduces a [[Bartholomew Roberts (fate)|stray servant]] who can't remember his true name, who goes by his character's name of Salazar.

title: owen_grady
body: The protagonist of the movie [[Jurassic World]].

title: john_hammond
body: Dr. John Alfred Hammond was the CEO of InGen and creator of [[Jurassic Park]]. He founded the company InGen and the Hammond Foundation. He had at least one daughter, two grandchildren (Tim and Lex Murphy), a sister (as Hammond's nephew has the surname of Ludlow, not Hammond) and a nephew, Peter Ludlow.

title: ian_malcolm
body: Dr. Ian Malcolm is a mathematician who specializes in a branch of mathematics known as "Chaos Theory". Malcolm is the tritagonist of the [[Jurassic Park]] franchise, serving as the tritagonist of Jurassic Park, the main protagonist of The Lost World: Jurassic Park, one of the three unseen overarching protagonists of [[Jurassic World]], a minor character in Jurassic World: Fallen Kingdom, and one of the three overarching protagonists of Jurassic World: Dominion. Malcolm appears in both novels by Michael Crichton. Malcolm serves as the mouthpiece of Crichton, who called Malcolm the "ironic commentator" on the action. In the movies, Malcolm is portrayed by Jeff Goldblum. Malcolm also appeared in most other Jurassic media like comics, video games and toy lines.

title: jurassic_world
body:

It revolves around a successor to the original park opening for business 22 years after the events of the first film. Again, chaos ensues when a hybrid [[dinosaur]], the [i]Indominus rex[/i], escapes its enclosure and terrorises the park.

She has a [[yellow skirt|yellow]] [[layered skirt]] consisting of a [[belt]], and [[white shorts]] [[shorts_under_skirt|underneath]]. It's a [[blue bikini]] with an [i]Alice in Wonderland[/i] theme, consisting of a [[white choker|white]] [[frilled choker]], a [[frilled bikini|frilled]] [[bikini top only|bikini top]] with [[frilled straps]] and a [[black ribbon]] on the back, a  [[blue skirt|blue]] [[frilled skirt|frilled]] [[bikini skirt]] with a white [[heart print|heart pattern]] worn over a black [[black bikini|black]] [[side-tie bikini bottom]], [[ankle strap]] and brown [[sandals]].

title: donkey_kong_country_2
body:
A 2D platforming game and sequel to [i][[Donkey Kong Country]][/i], released on the [[Super Nintendo]] in 1995 by Rare Ltd. 

The sidekick [[Diddy Kong]] is now leading the starring role as he and his girlfriend [[Dixie Kong]] must infiltrate Crocodile Isle in order to save [[Donkey Kong]] from the clutches of the Kremling Kuthroats.

title: donkey_kong_country_3
body:
Third and final entry of Rare Ltd's 2D Donkey Kong Country series, released on the [[Super Nintendo]] in 1996.

Sequel to [i][[Donkey Kong Country 2|Donkey Kong Country 2: Diddy's Kong Quest]][/i], with both [[Donkey Kong]] and [[Diddy Kong]] missing [[Dixie Kong]], along with [[Kiddy Kong]], travel to the Northern Kremisphere to find them while battling the Kremling Kreeps.

title: kerbal_space_program
body:
A popular space flight and construction simulator famed for its physics engine and scientific accuracy. You the player are in charge of a space program on the planet Kerbin, populated by a species of large-headed green people known as Kerbals. The goals are the construction and launching of spacecraft, exploration, and development of the solar system, or just blowing shit up and ebing a general failure (which is what the majority of the playerbase does). Has a large modding community with all kinds of historical and sci-fi content.

h4.External links

* "Official page":[https://kerbalspaceprogram.com/en/]

title: alice_(black_souls)
body:
Major character in [[Black Souls]] and Black Souls 2. Based on [[Alice in Wonderland]].

Can appear as several variations including Daughter Alice, Little Sister Alice, and Mother Alice in Black Souls 2.

[spoilers]
She's modeled after the real [[Alice Liddell (black souls)|]], who was into a relationship with Lewis Carroll until her father exiled the latter. Years later, Carroll became disgusted upon finding Alice's youthful beauty was gone and wished to go back to the old days, resulting in him being spirited away by Mary Sue and becoming Grimm.

Alice is a role played by The Crawling One a.k.a. [[Nyarlathotep]].
[[Daughter Alice (black souls)|]] is a role played by [[bandersnatch_(black_souls)| Bandersnatch ]]
[[Sister Alice (black souls)|]] is a role played by [[jubjub_(black_souls) | JubJub]]
[[Mother Alice (black souls)|]] is a role played by [[jabberwock_(black_souls)  | Jabberwock]]
[[Doll Alice (black souls)|]] is the Grand Guignol 
[/spoilers]

title: james_mccloud
body:
A character referenced in the original [[Star Fox]] and fully introduced in [[Star Fox 64]]. The father of [[Fox McCloud]] who was betrayed by [[Pigma Dengar]], leading to his death at the hands of [[Andross]].

In [[F-Zero]] he is instead the pilot of the Little Wyvern and leader of the mercenary unit called "Galaxy Dog". While being human his design is a clear homage to the Star Fox character.

title: angel_notes
body: An early [[Type_Moon]] work that takes place in the far future where the Earth is dead but people live still live on its surface. The remaining lifeforms are constantly under attack from the "Types" also known as "Ultimate Ones". The main characters are [[Gun_God]] the last unaltered human in the world, and [[V/V]], the reborn Type-Venus.
